author: The Wall Street Journal
description:
President Trump’s steep reciprocal tariffs against China went into effect at midnight Wednesday. What happens next at the largest port complex in the United States — the ports of Los Angeles and Long Beach — will foreshadow the economic aftershocks throughout the rest of the country. WSJ’s Paul Berger reports.
